race.comment: NAVY BUOY (1) exciting miler who will prove hard to catch again with Stanley's 3kg claim. Gave his rivals a galloping lesson with a slick on-pace win over this track and trip. Gets an even better set-up for this and expect to see him go to the next level. MOUNT BONA (4) progressive mare who was held up badly in the straight before sprouting wings with a gutsy victory over 1500m at Rosehill. Can race a little closer from the draw with Zac Lloyd taking the reins. Main danger. SNOWY (8) tough run from the outside gate when a respectable fifth to NAVY BUOY. Well placed with the claim and can take a hand in the finish. SACRED MISTRESS (5) finished behind MOUNT BONA and NAVY BUOY at her last two starts and meets them both better today with Grima's 3kg claim. Will push forward from the good gate and looks the value play in the race. PRIDE OF JEZZA (7) Wagga-trained gelding chasing a hat-trick. Tested from the draw but stays in the mix on the backup.
